<p id="mwBVU"><b id="mwBVY">General</b></p>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r853264625" about="#mwt644" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"refbegin","href":"./Template:Refbegin"},"params":{},"i":0}},"\n* [http://www.jewishencyclopedia.com/articles/14213-talmud/ Jewish Encyclopedia: Talmud]\n* [http://www.aish.com/literacy/jewishhistory/Crash_Course_in_Jewish_History_Part_39_-_Talmud.asp Jewish History: Talmud], aish.com\n* [https://www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org/jsource/Judaism/talmud_&amp;_mishna.html Talmud/Mishnah/Gemara], jewishvirtuallibrary.org\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20080705164241/http://www.law.miami.edu/library/judaicguide.php Jewish Law Research Guide], [[University of Miami]] Law Library\n* [http://ohr.edu/judaism/survey/survey.htm A survey of rabbinic literature], [[Ohr Somayach, Jerusalem|Ohr Somayach]]\n* [http://www.yibuffalo.org/divrei_torah/Intro_Talmud_06.pdf Introduction To The Talmud For The Novice], Rabbi M. Taub\n",{"template":{"target":{"wt":"refend","href":"./Template:Refend"},"params":{},"i":1}}]}' id="mwBVc"/><div class="refbegin   " style="" about="#mwt644" id="mwBVg">
