<p id="mwBWE"><b id="mwBWI">Manuscripts and textual variants</b></p>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r853264625" about="#mwt752" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"refbegin","href":"./Template:Refbegin"},"params":{},"i":0}},"\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20061212182252/http://jnul.huji.ac.il/dl/talmud/ Treasury of Talmudic Manuscripts, Jewish National and University Library]\n** [https://web.archive.org/web/20130126110223/http://jnul.huji.ac.il/dl/talmud/bavly/selectbavly.asp Treasury of Talmudic Manuscripts, search by tractate] – search engine for readings in different manuscripts (shows facsimile of individual pages)\n* [http://maagarim.hebrew-academy.org.il/Pages/PMain.aspx Academy of the Hebrew Language: The Historical Dictionary Project] – preferred manuscript for each tractate\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110218044050/http://www.bsb-muenchen.de/Babylonischer-Talmud.2519.0.html The Munich Talmud (Cod.hebr. 95)]\n* [http://www.lieberman-institute.com The Saul Lieberman Institute] – search engine (shows results in Hebrew/Aramaic text, not as facsimile)\n* [https://archive.is/20130416125610/http://www.yadharavherzog.org/program/manuscript-request-form-babli Yad Harav Herzog: manuscript request form] – search engine\n* [http://www.jewishmanuscripts.org/ Manuscripts and search engine hosted by the Friedberg Jewish Manuscript Society]\n",{"template":{"target":{"wt":"refend","href":"./Template:Refend"},"params":{},"i":1}}]}' id="mwBWM"/><div class="refbegin   " style="" about="#mwt752" id="mwBWQ">
<ul><li><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20061212182252/http://jnul.huji.ac.il/dl/talmud/">Treasury of Talmudic Manuscripts, Jewish National and University Library</a>
<ul><li><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20130126110223/http://jnul.huji.ac.il/dl/talmud/bavly/selectbavly.asp">Treasury of Talmudic Manuscripts, search by tractate</a> – search engine for readings in different manuscripts (shows facsimile of individual pages)</li></ul></li>
<li><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://maagarim.hebrew-academy.org.il/Pages/PMain.aspx">Academy of the Hebrew Language: The Historical Dictionary Project</a> – preferred manuscript for each tractate</li>
<li><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20110218044050/http://www.bsb-muenchen.de/Babylonischer-Talmud.2519.0.html">The Munich Talmud (Cod.hebr. 95)</a></li>
<li><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.lieberman-institute.com">The Saul Lieberman Institute</a> – search engine (shows results in Hebrew/Aramaic text, not as facsimile)</li>
<li><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://archive.is/20130416125610/http://www.yadharavherzog.org/program/manuscript-request-form-babli">Yad Harav Herzog: manuscript request form</a> – search engine</li>
<li><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.jewishmanuscripts.org/">Manuscripts and search engine hosted by the Friedberg Jewish Manuscript Society</a></li></ul>
</div>

